-- Philip Morris CR Plans to Raise Cigarette Prices, Pravo Reports
-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 2011-12-29T08:19:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-29/philip-morris-cr-plans-to-raise-cigarette-prices-pravo-reports.html
Philip Morris CR AS (TABAK)  will raise its
cigarette prices by as much as 4 koruna ($0.2) a pack beginning
in January because of the higher excise tax being introduced,
 Pravo  reported, citing company data.  The company will increase the price 2 koruna per a pack at
a minimum, the newspaper added.  To contact the reporter on this story: Lenka Ponikelska in
Prague   lponikelska1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  